CFC Insurance of Kenya Exempted From Ownership Law, Business Daily Reports

-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 
2011-02-23T04:17:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/cfc-insurance-of-kenya-exempted-from-ownership-law-business-daily-reports.html
CFC Insurance Holdings of Kenya was
exempted from a law that bars insurance companies from listing
on the Nairobi Stock Exchange if less than a third of their
shares are domestically owned, Business Daily reported.  The exemption was granted by Finance Minister Uhuru
Kenyatta, the Nairobi-based newspaper said today.  CFC Insurance is 24.95 percent owned by  Liberty Holdings
Ltd . of South Africa, 53.11 percent by  CFC Stanbic Holdings Ltd .
and 21.94 percent by domestic shareholders, it said. The company
plans to list later this year, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  